would you mind sharing your solution, I'm always interested in other people's C# solutions?
here's mine:

var s = Console.ReadLine();
var cleanString = Regex.Replace(s, "[^\\dA-Za-z]", "");
var answer = new string(cleanString.OrderBy(x => char.IsDigit(x) ? x + 100 : x).ToArray());

Console.WriteLine(answer);

I added +100 to the ascii code of digits so it can be sorted easily, I wonder what you did instead

var s = Console.ReadLine().Where(x=>(Char.IsLetter(x)||Char.IsDigit(x))).ToArray();
Array.Sort(s);
var result = new string(s.Where(Char.IsLetter).ToArray())+new string(s.Where(Char.IsDigit).ToArray());

Console.WriteLine(result);

ASCII sorting already puts capital letters before lowercase, but it doesn't put the numbers after the letters, so I just printed all the letters first then I printed all the numbers lol
